content:
The second step in decision optimization is to define the objective. The objective is your company goal, or the variable (or formula) to optimize recommendations for.

To specify the objective of the optimization:

Select whether you want to maximize or minimize the outcome variable.
Optionally, build a formula to modify the outcome variable by a numeric field on the Salesforce object.
Optionally, add a name to the objective. This name is used in the results dataset and components.
Click Next.

EXAMPLE
OPERATOR	DESCRIPTION	EXAMPLE
+ (Add)	Calculates the sum of two values	Attrition Impact [Account Overall Value + Expected Pipeline Value] * [Attrition Probability]
- (Subtract)	Calculates the difference of two values	Campaign Profit [Conversion Probability] * Customer Lifetime Value] - [Campaign Membership Cost]
* (Multiply)	Multiplies its values	Attrition Impact [Account Overall Value] * [Attrition Probability]
/ (Divide)	Divides its values	Attrition Impact [Expected Customer Lifetime Value] / [Campaign Cost]

Let us know so we can improve!
Yes
No
title: Defining Optimization Objective in Decision Optimization
